The paper deals with distributed computing and graph theory, which are both central topics in computer science. The focus on testing whether a graph is H-free, where H is a fixed 4-node graph, suggests that the paper belongs to the Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Graph Theory (cs.GT) sub-categories. The use of property testing techniques and the study of the complexity of testing different types of excluded subgraphs suggest that the paper could also belong to the Property Testing (cs.DS) and Network Economics (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the investigation of different types of generic algorithms for testing H-freeness suggests that the paper could also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
